WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

2
00:01:02.250 --> 00:01:04.415
<i>It started as a tropical disturbance.</i>

3
00:01:04.416 --> 00:01:07.624
<i>but in the last 24 hours.
Henry became a Category 2 hurricane…</i>

4
00:01:07.625 --> 00:01:10.749
<i>From the 11:00 a.m.
advisory from the National…</i>

5
00:01:10.750 --> 00:01:13.832
<i>…has Annieville
in the crosshairs of Henry.</i>

6
00:01:13.833 --> 00:01:15.832
<i>This is expected to be a major…</i>

7
00:01:15.833 --> 00:01:20.124
…<i>a buzz saw on satellite.
as it beelines toward our coast.</i>

8
00:01:20.125 --> 00:01:23.290
<i>It shows the storm
making landfall near Annieville.</i>

9
00:01:23.291 --> 00:01:26.082
<i>This is nothing to mess around with.</i>

10
00:01:26.083 --> 00:01:29.165
<i>This is the harbormaster
out of Beaufort Weather Tower.</i>

11
00:01:29.166 --> 00:01:30.707
<i>The National Hurricane Center</i>

12
00:01:30.708 --> 00:01:33.540
<i>issued hurricane
and storm-surge warnings for this area.</i>

13
00:01:33.541 --> 00:01:38.124
{\an8}<i>I repeat. hurricane and storm warnings
have been issued for this area.</i>

14
00:01:38.125 --> 00:01:41.249
{\an8}<i>Winds of up to 150 knots. seas to 60 feet.</i>

15
00:01:41.250 --> 00:01:44.165
{\an8}<i>and a 15-to-20-foot storm surge
are to be expected.</i>

16
00:01:44.166 --> 00:01:47.500
{\an8}<i>Weather threats
ramping up throughout the day--</i>

17
00:01:48.625 --> 00:01:50.415
{\an8}<i>Save our planet!</i>

18
00:01:50.416 --> 00:01:53.790
<i>It's the only one
with George. Garth. and Luke and Kate.</i>

19
00:01:53.791 --> 00:01:57.291
{\an8}- <i>Come on. now! Save us.</i>
- <i>97.8. WVD…</i>

20
00:02:36.916 --> 00:02:38.541
{\an8}Hey. Ray. how's it going?

21
00:02:40.541 --> 00:02:45.082
{\an8}Yeah. yeah. good. So. uh. today.
I was thinking something healthy.

22
00:02:45.083 --> 00:02:46.250
{\an8}Like a burger.

23
00:02:47.750 --> 00:02:49.958
{\an8}I mean. it still comes with tomato. right?

24
00:02:50.791 --> 00:02:53.666
{\an8}Mm-hmm. Yeah. no rush.
Just send it over as soon as…

25
00:02:55.500 --> 00:02:56.625
{\an8}Closing?

26
00:02:57.416 --> 00:02:58.458
{\an8}Now?

27
00:03:00.541 --> 00:03:01.999
But…

28
00:03:02.000 --> 00:03:04.291
I mean. it's just a little bit of…

29
00:03:05.916 --> 00:03:06.875
rain.

30
00:03:10.416 --> 00:03:14.708
{\an8}The grocery stores are still open. huh?
I guess I could just…

31
00:03:21.083 --> 00:03:23.041
{\an8}Yeah. I guess I could just walk.

32
00:03:25.291 --> 00:03:27.415
{\an8}Yeah. all right. stay safe.

33
00:03:27.416 --> 00:03:29.125
{\an8}Mm-hmm. You too. bye.

34
00:03:38.875 --> 00:03:39.958
{\an8}Get in.

35
00:03:40.916 --> 00:03:41.832
{\an8}Good.

36
00:03:41.833 --> 00:03:43.790
{\an8}- Gotta go.
- All right.

37
00:03:43.791 --> 00:03:47.000
{\an8}I've got half a tank!

38
00:03:53.958 --> 00:03:55.875
Whoa! Dakota!

39
00:03:57.458 --> 00:04:00.290
You shouldn't be out here. It's not safe.

40
00:04:00.291 --> 00:04:01.374
I needed food.

41
00:04:01.375 --> 00:04:03.790
I haven't seen you in forever.

42
00:04:03.791 --> 00:04:05.541
Not since your mom passed.

43
00:04:06.541 --> 00:04:09.083
{\an8}Look. they're saying
we should all get out of town.

44
00:04:11.791 --> 00:04:14.166
We got room in the car.

45
00:04:18.083 --> 00:04:19.290
Huh…

46
00:04:19.291 --> 00:04:21.583
{\an8}Mm…

47
00:04:28.708 --> 00:04:31.125
Woo-hoo!

48
00:04:35.833 --> 00:04:41.207
That looks like an 8.5
for my man. Ron Olsen!

49
00:04:41.208 --> 00:04:43.624
Ron!

50
00:04:43.625 --> 00:04:46.833
<i>Well burning the rubber
On my back tires…</i>

51
00:04:47.666 --> 00:04:50.250
- Ron!
- Ron!

52
00:04:51.833 --> 00:04:53.875
Ron?

53
00:04:54.708 --> 00:04:56.708
Hey. stop fooling around. Ron.

54
00:04:57.833 --> 00:04:58.832
Ron!

55
00:04:58.833 --> 00:05:01.874
<i>I gotta keep moving on down the road</i>

56
00:05:01.875 --> 00:05:04.707
Gotcha!

57
00:05:04.708 --> 00:05:07.207
<i>The highwayman…</i>

58
00:05:07.208 --> 00:05:08.916
It's the aqua-lungs. baby.

59
00:05:11.791 --> 00:05:13.291
This rain won't let up.

60
00:05:14.125 --> 00:05:15.833
Three more days of this.

61
00:05:16.666 --> 00:05:19.415
- Then school.
- I don't wanna think about it.

62
00:05:19.416 --> 00:05:21.708
Well. at least we gonna get fed every day.

63
00:05:24.041 --> 00:05:25.790
Okay. Will. you're up.

64
00:05:25.791 --> 00:05:28.582
Hold on. Quick gator-and-snake check.

65
00:05:28.583 --> 00:05:30.083
- Safety first.
- All right.

66
00:05:32.250 --> 00:05:34.916
We're good. Bombs away.

67
00:05:39.125 --> 00:05:43.000
What the hell do y'all think you're doing?
Get on down. little bastards!

68
00:05:45.333 --> 00:05:47.625
Don't you know
there's snakes in these swamps?

69
00:05:49.958 --> 00:05:51.625
Dee was on lookout. Mr. Olson.

70
00:05:52.625 --> 00:05:56.582
On lookout. What's she gonna be doing?
Spotting cottonmouths from up there?

71
00:05:56.583 --> 00:06:00.249
Who do you think's picking up
the goddamn doctor's bill?

72
00:06:00.250 --> 00:06:01.457
I'll tell you who.

73
00:06:01.458 --> 00:06:04.915
- Billy Olson right here.
- Like you'd ever take us to the doctor.

74
00:06:04.916 --> 00:06:06.500
What'd you say?

75
00:06:07.291 --> 00:06:09.375
What'd you say?

76
00:06:10.375 --> 00:06:13.416
Nothing. that's right.
Get your asses in the truck right now.

77
00:06:37.333 --> 00:06:38.500
All right.

78
00:06:40.000 --> 00:06:40.958
Come on.

79
00:07:01.625 --> 00:07:03.540
- Hey.
- Lisa. you're still here.

80
00:07:03.541 --> 00:07:06.749
But not for long.
I thought everything was closing down?

81
00:07:06.750 --> 00:07:11.207
Yeah. boss man wanted me to do
another load before they call it a day.

82
00:07:11.208 --> 00:07:13.707
Guess who's getting overtime?

83
00:07:13.708 --> 00:07:15.457
Where's Eric? He in the back?

84
00:07:15.458 --> 00:07:18.374
All right. Bob. see you later. Drive safe.

85
00:07:18.375 --> 00:07:19.458
Yeah. you too.

86
00:07:23.625 --> 00:07:25.582
<i>The wind is so strong.</i>

87
00:07:25.583 --> 00:07:30.083
<i>Now those waves will come out to be
maybe six or even seven feet tall.</i>

88
00:07:33.000 --> 00:07:34.957
No. I haven't told anyone yet.

89
00:07:34.958 --> 00:07:36.540
<i>Lisa. honey.</i>

90
00:07:36.541 --> 00:07:38.124
Mom. it's embarrassing.

91
00:07:38.125 --> 00:07:40.457
<i>How is it embarrassing for you?</i>

92
00:07:40.458 --> 00:07:42.540
<i>The jerk who left his pregnant fiancée</i>

93
00:07:42.541 --> 00:07:45.290
<i>to become. what.
a professional poker player?</i>

94
00:07:45.291 --> 00:07:47.165
Yep. And a DJ.

95
00:07:47.166 --> 00:07:50.165
<i>After he asked you to move
a thousand miles to his town?</i>

96
00:07:50.166 --> 00:07:51.624
<i>Ya know. I knew it.</i>

97
00:07:51.625 --> 00:07:55.874
<i>I knew it the moment I laid eyes
on that no-good son of a bitch.</i>

98
00:07:55.875 --> 00:08:00.332
- Can we just not talk about him?
- <i>Honey. did you give it any more thought?</i>

99
00:08:00.333 --> 00:08:01.957
- What?
<i>- You know. the birth.</i>

100
00:08:01.958 --> 00:08:05.665
<i>Like doing it in the tub.
in the water. like your sister did?</i>

101
00:08:05.666 --> 00:08:07.749
- Mom.
<i>- It'll still be in a hospital.</i>

102
00:08:07.750 --> 00:08:11.707
Yes. yes. in room 202 in a big. comfy bed

103
00:08:11.708 --> 00:08:14.915
with my perfectly-curated birth playlist.

104
00:08:14.916 --> 00:08:18.249
<i>Wait. why haven't you left town yet?</i>

105
00:08:18.250 --> 00:08:20.749
<i>They said the storm's gonna be really big.</i>

106
00:08:20.750 --> 00:08:24.832
They made us come into work today.
It wasn't my choice. but I'm leaving now.

107
00:08:24.833 --> 00:08:28.291
<i>How you gonna do that?
They said they closed the interstate.</i>

108
00:08:29.375 --> 00:08:30.374
Wait. what?

109
00:08:30.375 --> 00:08:32.249
<i>They just closed the interstate.</i>

110
00:08:32.250 --> 00:08:34.666
<i>Honey. you gotta get to higher ground.</i>

111
00:08:39.916 --> 00:08:40.958
Go. go. go!

112
00:08:41.958 --> 00:08:44.915
Dale. how bad is it out there?

113
00:08:44.916 --> 00:08:45.999
Pretty bad.

114
00:08:46.000 --> 00:08:50.540
Every fish south of Bermuda is bolting
north to get away from this storm.

115
00:08:50.541 --> 00:08:52.000
Must be a big one.

116
00:08:53.208 --> 00:08:55.541
Oh. yeah. that's coming in fast too.

117
00:08:57.791 --> 00:09:00.999
- Hey. did you get everyone tagged?
- Not even close.

118
00:09:01.000 --> 00:09:04.332
Too many of them
seem to be coming in with the storm.

119
00:09:04.333 --> 00:09:07.249
- Too many of them?
- The bull sharks.

120
00:09:07.250 --> 00:09:10.249
Spotted at least six
before I had to get out of there.

121
00:09:10.250 --> 00:09:12.707
Must be seeking shelter
in freshwater estuaries.

122
00:09:12.708 --> 00:09:14.499
- Dr. Edwards?
- Greg.

123
00:09:14.500 --> 00:09:16.457
- Hey.
- Thanks for the heads-up.

124
00:09:16.458 --> 00:09:18.166
- Of course.
- How bad is it?

125
00:09:23.500 --> 00:09:27.999
Yeah. If they ever consider
creating a Category 6. this would be it.

126
00:09:28.000 --> 00:09:29.540
It is a monster.

127
00:09:29.541 --> 00:09:31.833
- What are they calling it?
- Hurricane Henry.

128
00:09:32.958 --> 00:09:33.791
Henry.

129
00:09:34.708 --> 00:09:35.916
What would you call it?

130
00:09:36.541 --> 00:09:38.833
Uh… Ted Bundy?

131
00:09:39.750 --> 00:09:40.749
Oh.

132
00:09:40.750 --> 00:09:42.875
I've got to get hold of my niece.

133
00:09:43.916 --> 00:09:45.166
Okay. good idea.

134
00:09:59.750 --> 00:10:01.582
- <i>Hey.</i>
- You okay?

135
00:10:01.583 --> 00:10:03.416
Yeah. I was just. um…

136
00:10:05.208 --> 00:10:06.249
What's up?

137
00:10:06.250 --> 00:10:09.749
I was just calling to make sure
you have some way of leaving town.

138
00:10:09.750 --> 00:10:11.958
<i>If not. I could come pick you up in a bit.</i>

139
00:10:12.708 --> 00:10:16.915
- Thanks. but no need. I'm staying.
- They're saying it could be a Category 5.

140
00:10:16.916 --> 00:10:20.165
<i>It could land right on top of Annieville.
Which means</i>

141
00:10:20.166 --> 00:10:21.999
the house might come down on you.

142
00:10:22.000 --> 00:10:24.249
<i>You could be swimming inside your bedroom.</i>

143
00:10:24.250 --> 00:10:26.000
I dunno. Sounds kinda fun.

144
00:10:27.041 --> 00:10:28.708
<i>Look. you said it yourself.</i>

145
00:10:29.291 --> 00:10:31.291
"Could" or "might."

146
00:10:32.541 --> 00:10:35.707
It's what they always say.
and everything turns out fine.

147
00:10:35.708 --> 00:10:37.333
<i>The house is safe.</i>

148
00:10:38.541 --> 00:10:39.874
And so am I.

149
00:10:39.875 --> 00:10:42.374
<i>Look. I know you're hurting. Dakota.</i>

150
00:10:42.375 --> 00:10:44.207
<i>I miss your mother every day.</i>

151
00:10:44.208 --> 00:10:47.708
<i>But hiding in that house isn't going
to make the hurt go away.</i>

152
00:10:55.291 --> 00:10:58.958
You really suck at this parenting stuff.

153
00:10:59.666 --> 00:11:02.166
What can I say? I'm new at it.

154
00:11:03.125 --> 00:11:06.124
Yeah. I know.

155
00:11:06.125 --> 00:11:08.332
I'll be there as soon as I can. okay?

156
00:11:08.333 --> 00:11:10.458
<i>It'll only take a couple of hours.</i>

157
00:11:11.708 --> 00:11:12.583
Deal?

158
00:11:13.333 --> 00:11:14.500
Deal.

159
00:11:34.250 --> 00:11:36.415
You kids even listening to me?

160
00:11:36.416 --> 00:11:38.749
I'm telling you. in fact. I swear to God.

161
00:11:38.750 --> 00:11:42.165
you pull any of that shit again.
I'll send you back to foster care.

162
00:11:42.166 --> 00:11:43.749
<i>Stay tuned for…</i>

163
00:11:43.750 --> 00:11:47.249
Little shits. you don't know
your asses from a hole in the ground.

164
00:11:47.250 --> 00:11:50.999
<i>Law enforcement
have issued a mandatory evacuation.</i>

165
00:11:51.000 --> 00:11:53.457
<i>telling residents
they must leave their homes</i>

166
00:11:53.458 --> 00:11:56.999
<i>as the storm surge is expected
to hit shores within the next hour.</i>

167
00:11:57.000 --> 00:11:58.874
Lots of folks taking off.

168
00:11:58.875 --> 00:12:01.415
<i>- Breaking at this hour…</i>
- Are we heading out too?

169
00:12:01.416 --> 00:12:05.540
Bullshit. we are.
Ain't nothing but a little bit of weather.

170
00:12:05.541 --> 00:12:09.665
Wind and rain. and these jokers dump a log
in their panties. run for the hills.

171
00:12:09.666 --> 00:12:10.875
<i>…biggest threat with…</i>

172
00:12:12.208 --> 00:12:15.499
<i>If it don't twang. it ain't my thing</i>

173
00:12:15.500 --> 00:12:19.790
<i>If it don't hang
Like the midnight train</i>

174
00:12:19.791 --> 00:12:22.124
<i>Or cry like a steel</i>

175
00:12:22.125 --> 00:12:24.957
<i>Bending my old heartstrings</i>

176
00:12:24.958 --> 00:12:28.082
<i>Listen! I said Brooke is your mother's--</i>

177
00:12:28.083 --> 00:12:31.124
<i>Get your finger out of my face!</i>

178
00:12:31.125 --> 00:12:32.790
- <i>Out!</i>
- <i>All!</i>

179
00:12:32.791 --> 00:12:36.457
<i>- I'm not crazy! You were eating my face!
- Gotta get out of the room.</i>

180
00:12:36.458 --> 00:12:39.500
<i>- No. absolutely not.
- Call the police right now.</i>

181
00:12:40.333 --> 00:12:43.874
<i>Look at the radar
of Hurricane Henry one hour ago.</i>

182
00:12:43.875 --> 00:12:47.665
<i>It's a Category 2. and then it hits
record warm waters off the coast.</i>

183
00:12:47.666 --> 00:12:51.041
<i>and boom. it becomes a Category 5.</i>

184
00:12:51.916 --> 00:12:55.332
<i>Two swimmers were attacked
on Myrtle Beach this morning</i>

185
00:12:55.333 --> 00:12:58.000
<i>by what onlookers say was a large shark.</i>

186
00:13:01.083 --> 00:13:04.250
- <i>Get her!</i>
- <i>Gonna get you!</i>

187
00:13:07.958 --> 00:13:12.832
- <i>That's my girl.
- Okay. let me show you.</i>

188
00:13:12.833 --> 00:13:13.833
<i>Okay.</i>

189
00:13:15.666 --> 00:13:18.124
<i>See? It's stable.</i>

190
00:13:18.125 --> 00:13:20.540
<i>Much easier to hit.</i>

191
00:13:20.541 --> 00:13:22.665
<i>One more time?</i>

192
00:13:22.666 --> 00:13:24.707
- <i>You try.</i>
- <i>Okay.</i>

193
00:13:24.708 --> 00:13:26.832
<i>You can do it. Good.</i>

194
00:13:26.833 --> 00:13:29.333
<i>Try your dad.</i>

195
00:13:30.291 --> 00:13:32.165
<i>Oh. boy. Ow!</i>

196
00:13:32.166 --> 00:13:34.332
<i>- Bull's-eye!
- Yes!</i>

197
00:13:34.333 --> 00:13:37.540
<i>You got him.</i>

198
00:13:37.541 --> 00:13:38.958
<i>You're amazing.</i>

199
00:14:01.583 --> 00:14:03.499
What if the windows break?

200
00:14:03.500 --> 00:14:05.499
Reinforced glass. all right?

201
00:14:05.500 --> 00:14:08.499
I installed them bad boys myself.

202
00:14:08.500 --> 00:14:11.666
That. the waterproof wiring.
and a generator.

203
00:14:12.333 --> 00:14:14.375
So quit your goddamn worrying.

204
00:14:19.375 --> 00:14:20.832
It's coming down out there!

205
00:14:20.833 --> 00:14:24.915
I caught them little bastards
up by the creek swimming with damn snakes.

206
00:14:24.916 --> 00:14:28.290
Swear to God. they do not have
the sense they were born with.

207
00:14:28.291 --> 00:14:29.957
Do not know why I bother.

208
00:14:29.958 --> 00:14:32.874
Oh. need I remind you. baby. huh? Huh?

209
00:14:32.875 --> 00:14:35.374
Uncle Sam. he does pay out now and then.

210
00:14:35.375 --> 00:14:36.457
Yeah.

211
00:14:36.458 --> 00:14:37.540
We're hungry.

212
00:14:37.541 --> 00:14:39.833
- Goddamn!
- Where did you come from?

213
00:14:41.291 --> 00:14:43.125
Are those steaks?

214
00:14:44.750 --> 00:14:46.541
It's none of your damn business!

215
00:14:48.875 --> 00:14:49.916
Here.

216
00:14:51.416 --> 00:14:53.708
Just like Mama used to make.

217
00:14:54.291 --> 00:14:57.833
Hey. you know goddamn well
that this basement's off-limits.

218
00:14:58.416 --> 00:15:00.166
- Right.
- Get your ass up there.

219
00:15:08.166 --> 00:15:11.750
Dr. Edwards! Do you mind
if we speak to you for a moment?

220
00:15:13.166 --> 00:15:16.958
Sorry. just… Any comment
on the shark incident this morning?

221
00:15:17.541 --> 00:15:18.375
What incident?

222
00:15:19.375 --> 00:15:23.040
<i>A couple at Myrtle Beach
was attacked by a great white shark.</i>

223
00:15:23.041 --> 00:15:26.874
<i>Eyewitnesses saw the whole thing.
spotted at least two sharks on the scene.</i>

224
00:15:26.875 --> 00:15:28.832
Great whites don't hunt in packs.

225
00:15:28.833 --> 00:15:31.290
What you're describing
sounds like bull sharks.

226
00:15:31.291 --> 00:15:35.457
<i>Bull sharks. yes. The hyenas of the ocean.</i>

227
00:15:35.458 --> 00:15:37.832
<i>Thrives in salt and fresh water.</i>

228
00:15:37.833 --> 00:15:40.540
<i>got 12 times as powerful bite
as most sharks.</i>

229
00:15:40.541 --> 00:15:43.290
<i>and eats about anything they come across.</i>

230
00:15:43.291 --> 00:15:46.124
Not necessarily accurate
and greatly exaggerated.

231
00:15:46.125 --> 00:15:47.540
Thank you very much.

232
00:15:47.541 --> 00:15:48.749
- So…
- Come on.

233
00:15:48.750 --> 00:15:52.625
The risk of shark attacks is on the rise.
according to the expert.

234
00:16:01.416 --> 00:16:02.625
